- **Basics**: Gravel islands (not tundra-damaging) for drilling pads. "Clean" = minimal footprint: Recycle waste, use geofoam insulation, remove contaminated gravel.
- **Slope Context**: North Slope (Arctic oil/gas) has 1,000+ old pads. BP cleaning Foggy Island Bay (2022–2025): Remove pits, oil-soaked gravel—$10M+ project.
- **Battery Link**: Pads for "battery minerals" mining (cobalt/nickel from Slope-adjacent sites). Hilcorp's 2024 pad expansion (25 wells) uses "clean" tech for EV supply chain.

