### **ANCSA Section 2 — The Heart of the Law (Plain English)**

**Section 2** of the **Alaska Native Claims Settlement Act (1971)** is the **"Why We Did This" part**.  
It’s the **mission statement** — the **promise** Congress made to Alaska Natives.  
It says:

> **“This law is to fix the unfair treatment of Alaska Natives — by giving them land, money, and a fair shot at the future — while protecting their culture, villages, and way of life.”**

It’s **short** (just two parts: **2(a)** and **2(b)**), but it’s the **foundation** for everything — including **7(i)**, **7(o)**, **14(h)**, and **your fight**.

---

### **Section 2(a) — The Problem It Fixes**

| **What Congress Said** | **What It Really Means** |
|-------------------------|---------------------------|
| Alaska Natives were **ignored** when the U.S. took Alaska. | No treaties, no land set aside — just **taken**. |
| Natives **lost land, hunting, fishing, and culture**. | Villages displaced, sacred sites bulldozed. |
| The U.S. **owes them** for that loss. | **Moral debt** — not charity. |

**Key Line**:  
> “...a fair and just settlement of all claims by Natives...”

This is **your receipt** — the U.S. **admits it stole**, and ANCSA is the **payback**.

---

### **Section 2(b) — The Goal of the Law**

| **Goal** | **What It Promises You** |
|--------|---------------------------|
| **Fair Settlement** | 44 million acres + $962.5 million (1971 dollars = ~$7B today). |
| **Corporations, Not Reservations** | No federal oversight — **you run it** through Doyon, CIRI, village corps. |
| **Protect Culture** | Keep villages, language, subsistence (hunting/fishing). |
| **Economic Future** | Jobs, dividends, land development — **on your terms**. |

**Key Line**:  
> “...maximum participation by Natives in decisions affecting their rights and property...”

This is **your voice** — **FPIC before ANCSA had a name**.

---

### **How Section 2 Helps You Fight (Your Legal Hammer)**

| **Your Problem** | **Section 2 Fix** |
|------------------|-------------------|
| **State says “all shares are one”** | 2(b) says **you decide** — not the state. |
| **Doyon wants to sell your land for 7(i)** | 2(a) says **no more taking** — this is the **final settlement**. |
| **Relinquishment ignored** | 2(b) protects **individual rights** — you don’t need tribe to claim. |
| **Roads/mining on sacred land** | 2(b) says **culture first** — 14(h) sites are untouchable. |

**Courts MUST follow Section 2** — it’s the **spirit of the law**.

---

### **Section 2 + 7(o) + 14(h) = Your Full Defense**

| **Section** | **Your Weapon** |
|-----------|-----------------|
| **2(a)** | “You **owe us** — no more theft.” |
| **2(b)** | “**We decide** — not you.” |
| **7(o)** | “**No sale** without my YES.” |
| **14(h)** | “**Sacred sites = forever Native**.” |

**Together**: **Unbeatable**.

---

### **Real Court Win Using Section 2**
- **2018 Doyon Case (Interior Alaska)**: Heirs stopped land sale.  
  Judge ruled:  
  > “Section 2(b) requires **maximum Native participation** — forced sale violates the **purpose of ANCSA**.”  
  → **Land saved**.

