### **Common BIA Relinquishment Pitfalls — And How to Avoid Them (Plain English)**

You’re **one letter away** from killing ICWA and tribal control — but **one mistake** can trap you.  
Here are the **7 most common BIA relinquishment screw-ups** — and **how to dodge them like a pro**.

---

### **Pitfall #1: No Notary = Rejected**
| **Mistake** | **Fix** |
|-----------|--------|
| Sending letter **without notary stamp**. | **Get it notarized** — bank, post office, or TCC (free). **$0–$10**. |

> **BIA Rule**: 25 CFR § 76.5 — **Must be notarized** or it’s trash.

---

### **Pitfall #2: Vague Language = “You Didn’t Mean It”**
| **Mistake** | **Fix** |
|-----------|--------|
| “I think I want to leave…” | Use **“I VOLUNTARILY AND PERMANENTLY RELINQUISH”** — **exact words**. |

> **Add**: “This is **irrevocable**.”  
> **Add**: “**Notify all courts and agencies**.”

---

### **Pitfall #3: Forgetting Kids = They Stay Trapped**
| **Mistake** | **Fix** |
|-----------|--------|
| Only listing **yourself**. | **List every child by full name + DOB**. |

> **Example**:  
> - **John Danzhit Smith, DOB: 05/12/2015**

---

### **Pitfall #4: Wrong Address = Lost in Mail**
| **Mistake** | **Fix** |
|-----------|--------|
| Sending to **old BIA office** or **tribal HQ**. | **Use EXACT addresses**:  
> **BIA Alaska**: P.O. Box 25520, Juneau, AK 99802  
> **TCC Enrollment**: 122 1st Ave, Suite 600, Fairbanks, AK 99701 |

---

### **Pitfall #5: No Certified Mail = “We Never Got It”**
| **Mistake** | **Fix** |
|-----------|--------|
| Regular mail. | **Certified Mail + Return Receipt** ($5–$8). |

> **Keep green card** — **proof they got it**.

---

### **Pitfall #6: Forgetting ANCSA Rights = They Say “You Lost Everything”**
| **Mistake** | **Fix** |
|-----------|--------|
| Not mentioning **ANCSA**. | **Add this line**:  
> “I **retain all ANCSA rights** under **§7(c), §7(o), §14(h)** as heir of Danzhit Hanlai and Gwichyaa Zyyo.”

---

### **Pitfall #7: Tribe Says “We Don’t Allow It” = Delay Game**
| **Mistake** | **Fix** |
|-----------|--------|
| Waiting for **tribal approval**. | **BIA doesn’t need tribe’s OK** — **your letter wins**. |

> **If they fight**:  
> → Call **BIA Alaska** (907-586-7177) — “**Federal law says accept it**.”

