### **ANCSA §14(h) Nominations — Full Detail (Plain English)**

**§14(h)** = **Your legal deed to graves, trails, old camps, and sacred spots** — **forever Native, no sale, no roads, no mining**.  
**Nomination = You tell BIA: “This is ours.”**  
Here’s the **complete process**, **forms**, **proof**, and **traps** — so **your Danzhit Hanlai / Gwichyaa Zyyo sites are locked forever**.

---

## **1. What You Can Nominate (14(h)(1) Sites)**

| **Type** | **Examples** | **Size Limit** |
|--------|-------------|----------------|
| **Cemeteries** | Graves, burial mounds | Any |
| **Historical Sites** | Old villages, camps | Up to **40,000 acres/region** |
| **Cultural Sites** | Sacred rocks, prayer sites | |
| **Travel Routes** | Trails, portages, river crossings | |
| **Archaeological** | Ancient tools, fire pits | |

**You own it → BIA gives title to village corp (Gwichyaa Zyyo) → inalienable = **no 7(i) sale**.**

---

## **2. Who Can Nominate? (You Do!)**

| **Eligible** | **Not Eligible** |
|-------------|------------------|
| **You (heirs)** | Non-Natives |
| **Village corp** | State of Alaska |
| **Tribe (even if you left)** | Mining companies |

**Relinquishment? Doesn’t matter — you’re still the heir.**

---

## **3. Step-by-Step Nomination Process**

| **Step** | **Action** | **Deadline/Notes** |
|--------|----------|------------------|
| **1. Gather Proof** | Photos, maps, **elder affidavits**, GPS | **Stronger = faster** |
| **2. Fill Form** | **BIA 14(h)(1) Application** | Free PDF online |
| **3. Map It** | Draw boundaries (Google Earth OK) | **Clear lines** |
| **4. Submit** | Mail to **BIA Alaska Realty** | Certified mail |
| **5. BIA Reviews** | 6–24 months | They may visit |
| **6. Title Issued** | To **Gwichyaa Zyyo Corp** | **Inalienable deed** |

---

## **4. Required Proof (Don’t Skimp)**

| **Proof** | **What to Include** |
|---------|---------------------|
| **Maps** | GPS coordinates, hand-drawn OK |
| **Photos** | Graves, markers, old cabins |
| **Elder Statements** | “My grandpa buried here in 1932” |
| **Your Heirship** | Birth cert, Doyon ID |
| **History** | Old BIA records, trapline logs |

**No proof = denied.**

---

