### **ANCSA Section 14(c) Allotments — Your Village Corp’s Promise to You (Plain English)**

**§14(c)** = **“We’ll give you land inside the village — no questions.”**  
It’s the **village corporation’s legal duty** to transfer **small plots** (usually **1–5 acres**) to **you, your family, and community** — **for free**, **forever**, **no 7(i) sale**.

---

## **1. What 14(c) Gives You**

| **Type** | **Who Gets It** | **Size** |
|--------|----------------|--------|
| **Home Lots** | You + family | 1–3 acres |
| **Community Use** | Church, clinic, graveyard | Up to 1,280 acres total |
| **Traditional Camps** | Subsistence users | 1–5 acres |
| **Municipal Reserves** | City/tribe services | Varies |

**Title**: **Fee simple** — **you own it**, **not the corp**.

---

## **2. Who Qualifies? (You Do!)**

| **Eligible** | **Not Eligible** |
|-------------|------------------|
| **Village residents in 1971** | Outsiders |
| **Heirs of residents** | Non-Natives |
| **Traditional users** | Corps themselves |

**Relinquishment? Doesn’t matter** — **you’re still heir**.

---

## **3. 14(c) Process — Step by Step**

| **Step** | **Action** | **Who Does It** |
|--------|----------|---------------|
| **1. Village Corp Surveys** | Maps all 14(c) claims | **Gwichyaa Zyyo Corp** |
| **2. You File Claim** | Submit **14(c) application** | **You** |
| **3. Corp Approves** | Board votes YES | **Corp board** |
| **4. BIA Records** | Files deed | **BIA** |
| **5. You Get Title** | **Fee patent** in your name | **You own it** |

**Deadline**: **No deadline** — but **file now** before corp sells.

---

## **4. Required 14(c) Claim Form (Key Info)**

| **Field** | **Fill Like This** |
|---------|-------------------|
| **Claimant** | [Your Name], heir of Danzhit Hanlai |
| **Use** | “Primary residence” or “traditional camp” |
| **Location** | Lot 5, Block 2, Fort Yukon |
| **Size** | 2.5 acres |
| **Proof** | Photos, elder letter, 1971 residency |

**Form**: Village corp provides — **call Gwichyaa Zyyo**.

---

