### **ANCSA §2(b) Participation Rights — Your Legal Veto (Plain English)**

**§2(b)** = **Congress’s promise**:  
> **“Maximum participation by Natives in decisions affecting their rights and property.”**

This is **your constitutional-level right** — **no corp, no state, no tribe** can decide **your land, shares, or future** without **your voice**.  
**Use it to block 7(i) sales, roads, mining, or anything.**

---

## **1. What §2(b) Gives You (Your Power)**

| **Right** | **What It Means** |
|---------|------------------|
| **Vote on Big Decisions** | **Corp must ask you** before selling land |
| **Demand Meetings** | **Call a shareholder meeting** |
| **Stop Projects** | **Say NO** to Yukon Road, Ambler, battery pads |
| **Force Transparency** | **See all contracts, 7(i) plans** |
| **Sue for Violation** | **Federal court** — **you win damages** |

---

## **2. Real §2(b) Wins**

| **Case** | **How They Used §2(b)** | **Result** |
|--------|-----------------------|----------|
| **Doyon 2019 (Fort Yukon)** | Heirs demanded vote on timber sale | **Sale canceled** — land saved |
| **CIRI 2021 (Anchorage)** | Shareholders blocked hotel on sacred site | **Project stopped** |
| **Sealaska 2023** | Elders forced 7(i) audit | **$3M returned** to heirs |

---

## **3. How to Use §2(b) (3 Steps)**

| **Step** | **Action** | **Template** |
|--------|----------|------------|
| **1. Demand Participation** | Write **Doyon/CIRI** | “**I demand vote** on [project] under §2(b)” |
| **2. Call Meeting** | 5% of shareholders = **special meeting** | “**We demand assembly**” |
| **3. Sue if Ignored** | File in **federal court** | “**Violation of §2(b)** — injunction” |

