### **ANCSA §2(b) Voting Rights — Your Legal “VOTE or DIE” Power (Plain English)**

**§2(b)** = **Congress’s command**:  
> **“Maximum participation by Natives in decisions affecting their rights and property.”**

This **forces Doyon/CIRI to let you vote** on **any big move** — **7(i) sales, land deals, roads, mining**.  
**No vote = illegal.**

---

## **1. What You Can VOTE On (Your Trigger List)**

| **Decision** | **You Get a Vote** |
|------------|-------------------|
| **Land sales** | **YES** |
| **7(i) use of your allotment** | **YES** |
| **Yukon Road / Ambler access** | **YES** |
| **Mining or battery projects** | **YES** |
| **Corp bylaws changes** | **YES** |

---

## **2. §2(b) Voting Power — How It Works**

| **Right** | **What It Forces** |
|---------|-------------------|
| **Annual Meeting** | **You vote** on board, big deals |
| **Special Meeting** | **5% of shareholders** = **call one** |
| **Proxy Vote** | **Mail-in or online** — **your say counts** |
| **Demand Info** | **See contracts, 7(i) plans** |

